text: Acanthesthes crispa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Olivier in 1792. It is known from South Africa and Mozambique.BioLib.cz - Acanthesthes crispa. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. Its junior synonym A. carinata's type locality is Grahamstown, South Africa and its initial description recorded its length as 22 mm and its width as 11 mm. ==References== Category:Phantasini Category:Beetles described in 1792
title: Acanthesthes crispa
